Business Requirements for OptiCrop: Smart Agricultural Production Optimization Engine
Functional Requirements
The system shall allow farmers to register and log in securely.
The system shall store farmer, farm, and field information.
The system shall collect soil data (N, P, K, pH, moisture).
The system shall collect weather information (temperature, humidity, rainfall).
The system shall recommend the most suitable crop using AI/ML models.
The system shall predict expected crop yield.
The system shall recommend the appropriate fertilizer type and quantity.
The system shall generate irrigation schedules based on soil moisture and weather conditions.
The system shall detect plant diseases from uploaded leaf images.
The system shall provide treatment recommendations for detected diseases.
The system shall generate reports and maintain historical farming records.
The system shall display recommendations through a user-friendly dashboard.
Non-Functional Requirements
The system should provide recommendations within a few seconds.
The system should ensure secure storage of farmer and farm data.
The system should be scalable to support multiple users simultaneously.
The system should be reliable with high availability.
The system should provide accurate AI/ML predictions.
The user interface should be simple and easy to use.
The system should be compatible with desktop and mobile devices.
The system should support regular updates of AI models and datasets.
Data Requirements

The system requires the following data:

Farmer details
Farm and field information
Soil nutrient values (N, P, K, pH)
Soil moisture
Weather data
Crop information
Historical yield data
Fertilizer information
Plant disease images
AI-generated recommendation history
Business Rules
Each farmer can register multiple farms.
Each farm can contain multiple fields.
Crop recommendations shall be generated based on soil and weather conditions.
Fertilizer recommendations shall be based on soil nutrient analysis.
Irrigation recommendations shall consider soil moisture and weather forecasts.
Disease detection shall analyze uploaded crop leaf images.
All recommendations shall be stored for future reference.
Only authenticated users can access their farm data and reports.
Expected Business Outcomes
Increased crop productivity.
Improved crop selection accuracy.
Reduced fertilizer and water wastage.
Early detection of plant diseases.
Accurate crop yield prediction.
Lower farming costs.
Better resource utilization.
Enhanced decision-making through AI-driven recommendations.
Promotion of sustainable and precision agriculture.
